definition.value: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate group of any O-(S-[2S,4S,6S]-2,4,6-trimethyl-very-long-chain fatty acyl-pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine residue
A citrate anion obtained by deprotonation of the three carboxy groups as well as the hydroxy group of citric acid.
An aminopyridine that is 3-aminopyridine carrying an additional iodo substituent at postion 4.
An ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3,4-dihydroxybenzoic acid with ethanol. It is the anti-oxidative component of peanut seed testa.

An EC 1.14.11.* (oxidoreductase acting on paired donors, 2-oxoglutarate as one donor, incorporating 1 atom each of oxygen into both donors) inhibitor that interferes with the action of procollagen-proline dioxygenase (EC 1.14.11.2).
A methyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3,4-dihydroxybenzoic acid with methanol.
A carbohydrate acid derivative anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any beta-D-glucuronoside.
Any organic molecular entity that acts as a glucuronate acceptor.

A member of the class of tetraphenes that is tetraphene in which the hydrogen at position 1 has been replaced by a hydroxy group. It is a urinary hydroxylated metabolite of tetraphene (benzo[a]anthracene).
A pentacyclic triterpenoid with formula C30H48O4, originally isolated from Tripterygium hypoglaucum.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid with formula C30H48O4, originally isolated from Tripterygium wilfordii and Tripterygium hypoglaucum.
A hexacyclic triterpenoid with formula C30H48O4, originally isolated from Tripterygium wilfordii and Tripterygium hypoglaucum.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid with formula C30H48O4, originally isolated from Akebia quinata and Stauntonia hexaphylla.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid with formula C30H50O2, originally isolated from Tripterygium hypoglaucum.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid with formula C30H48O4, originally isolated from Tripterygium doianum.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid with formula C29H42O4, originally isolated from Tripterygium sp.
A hydroxybenzo[c]phenanthrene that is benzo[c]phenanthrene in which the hydrogen at position 1 has been replaced by a hydroxy group. A metabolite of benzo[c]phenanthrene.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid with formula C29H38O5, originally isolated from the stems of Tripterygium regelii.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid with formula C29H38O4, originally isolated from the root bark of Tripterygium wilfordii.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid with formula C30H44O5, originally isolated from the bark of Tripterygium wilfordii.
A dihydroagarofuran sesquiterpenoid with formula C36H45NO17 that is isolated from the root bark of Tripterygium hypoglaucum.
A sesquiterpene alkaloid with formula C36H45NO17, that is isolated from the root bark of Tripterygium hypoglaucum.
A sesquiterpene alkaloid that is isolated from Tripterygium wilfordii and Tripterygium hypoglaucum.
A sesquiterpene alkaloid that is isolated from Tripterygium wilfordii and Tripterygium hypoglaucum.
A sesquiterpene alkaloid that is isolated from Tripterygium wilfordii and Tripterygium hypoglaucum.

A sesquiterpene alkaloid that has been isolated from Tripterygium wilfordii and exhibits immunosuppressive and insecticidal properties. It was found to be identical with euonine, previously isolated from Euonymous sieboldiana.
A sesquiterpene alkaloid that is isolated from Tripterygium wilfordii.
A sesquiterpene alkaloid that is isolated from Tripterygium hypoglaucum.
A sesquiterpene alkaloid that is isolated from Tripterygium hypoglaucum.
A sesquiterpene alkaloid that is isolated from Tripterygium hypoglaucum.
A hydroxychrysene that is chrysene in which the hydrogen at position 1 has been replaced by a hydroxy group. It is a metabolite of the polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon chrysene.
A sesquiterpene alkaloid that is isolated from Euonymus Sieboldiana.
A sesquiterpene alkaloid that is isolated from Tripterygium forrestii, Platanus chiapensis and Maytenus chiapensis.
A sesquiterpene alkaloid that is isolated from Tripterygium hypoglaucum and Tripterygium wilfordii.
A sesquiterpene alkaloid that is isolated from Tripterygium wilfordii.
A sesquiterpene alkaloid that is isolated from the stem of Tripterygium regelii.
A member of the class of hydroxypiperidines that is piperidine carrying a hydroxymethyl substituent at position 2 as well as two hydroxy substituents at positions 3 and 4 (the 2R,3R,4S-diastereomer).
A member of the class of phenols that has a chrysene skeleton which is substituted by one of more hydroxy groups.
A member of the class of psoralens that is (-)-marmesin in which the hydroxy hydrogen is replaced by a beta-D-glucosyl residue.

A member of the class of coumarins that is 7-methoxycoumarin in which the hydrogen at position 6 has been replaced by a 1,2,3-trihydroxy-3-methylbutyl group (the 1R,2S stereoisomer). Originally isolated from the roots of Angelica pubescens, angelitriol shows strong inhibitory effects on human platelet aggregation.
A dipeptide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-alanine with the alpha-amino group of L-lysine.
A hydroxychrysene that is chrysene in which the hydrogen at position 2 has been replaced by a hydroxy group. It is a metabolite of the polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon chrysene.
A hydroxychrysene that is chrysene in which the hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a hydroxy group. It is a metabolite of the polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon chrysene.
A hydroxychrysene that is chrysene in which the hydrogen at position 4 has been replaced by a hydroxy group. It is a metabolite of the polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon chrysene.
A hydroxychrysene that is chrysene in which the hydrogen at position 6 has been replaced by a hydroxy group. It is a metabolite of the polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon chrysene.
a thioether linkage between a cys and phe residue.
